gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.variable

Class PopulatedVariableGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.variable.PopulatedVariableGroup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<PopulatedVariableGroup>

    public final class PopulatedVariableGroup
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<PopulatedVariableGroup>

    Contains a list of Variables in the same VariableGroup. This is a separate class from VariableGroup because the latter is a persistent entity.

    Per Effective Java Item 17, this class is marked final because it was not designed for inheritance.

    • Method Detail

      • getVariables

        public java.util.List<Variable> getVariables()

        Returns the List of Variables, always containing at least 1 Variable. All contained Variables will have equal VariableGroups. The collection itself is immutable, though the variables themselves are not.

        Order is preserved from construction.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(PopulatedVariableGroup o)

        Compares this PopulatedVariableGroup with another. Comparison is based only on each object's associated VariableGroup.

        Not consistent with equals: two PopulatedVariableGroups with different sets of variables from the same group are non-equal but will compare as equal.
